    "roas": "REAL as of 2026-07-11 (previously null \u2014 store had no LTV data). roas_standard/roas_conservative computed from facility_day's MSR-native LTV/leads/conversion columns + real ad_spend, same formula as nectar/roas.py (validated: matches the already-confirmed live-pull June ROAS figures exactly). Reflects 2026-06 (the latest month with real ad_spend) for 23 ad-running facilities; the other 6 run no ads and correctly show roas_standard=null, not a fabricated 0.",
    "revenue_yoy": "REAL as of 2026-07-11 (previously null). Current vs. the SAME CALENDAR DATE last year, SAME-STORE ONLY (backfill_history.py imported 13 months of already-cached MSR history + one live same-date-prior-year pull). All 29 facilities had valid prior-year data \u2014 none excluded.",
    "revenue_mtd_accuracy": "FIXED 2026-07-11: revenue_authoritative now reads net_revenue.revenue_mtd verbatim off each facility's latest MSR snapshot (facility_day.revenue_mtd_msr), replacing the SUM(revenue_net)-over-days proxy that overstated MTD by ~15-27% (see README.md).",
    "leads_by_channel_mtd": "real per-channel counts, but facility_day_leadsource only started 2026-07-09 \u2014 as of 2026-07-11 it covers a partial window, not the full MTD leads_total figure; fills out day by day. (Unrelated to this pass's fixes \u2014 still gapped.)",
    "ad_spend_month": "reflects 2026-06, the latest CLOSED month \u2014 ad spend refreshes monthly at month-close, not on this twice-daily cadence. roas above uses the SAME month so spend and leads/LTV are period-coherent.",
    "rent_per_sqft": "FIXED 2026-07-11: now reads space_metrics.average_rent_area.occupied verbatim (Travis's \"economic occupancy $/sqft\") off each facility's latest MSR snapshot \u2014 captured on every ingest, no derived/summed proxy.",
    "units_total_and_net_move_ins_ytd": "ADDED 2026-07-11 for the facility map hover cards. facilities[].units_total is the latest facility_day snapshot (store-native, no extra API call). facilities[].net_move_ins_ytd is read verbatim from a live MSR pull's own rental_metrics.net_count_movein_moveout.ytd field (same reasoning as nectar/sil1_daily_card.py) because facility_day's daily move_ins/move_outs only cover 2026-07-01 onward, too short a window to sum a full-year YTD locally. All 29 facilities returned a real YTD figure.",
    "revenue_history_backfill": "13 months of MSR history (2025-05 through 2026-06, monthly grain) are now in facility_day, reused from nectar.history's existing snapshots/history_<key>.jsonl cache (zero new API calls for 12 of those months) plus one live pull each for 2026-06-30 and last year's same calendar date. Historical LTV was NOT backfilled beyond the current month + 2026-06 \u2014 a ROAS trend chart would need that; revenue/occupancy trend is ready for a future date-range selector today."
  }
